Sandra Tobon

1 HALLOWEEN DATA

1.1 What is the dataset about?

Every year around the world but mainly in USA and Canada, is a poll that ask people about how if they Join, Despair or Meh, some general candies; the grade of conecction that they have with specifics famous person; some question about cultural and publicity things, and some personal questions.

For this exercise is only neccesary the information about the candies.

1.2 Data clean proccess

  • Clean the age column
  • Clean the country column, for this is very helpfull the states column. (2016 - 2017)
  • Select the columns for the analysis
  • Pivot longer (candies and the preferences)
  • Add a year column in each data set.
  • Add some columns that 2015 data set didn’t have.
  • Unit the 3 data sets and filter some information without relation to a real candy

1.3 Solutions to the questions

  1. Total number of candy ratings given across the three years
halloween_candies %>%
  group_by(candies_food) %>%
  summarise(n_candies_ratings = n()) %>%
  summarise(total_candies_ratings = sum(n_candies_ratings))
halloween_candies %>%
    group_by(candies_food) %>%
    summarise(n_candies = n_distinct(candies_food)) %>%
    summarise(total_candies_analysis = sum(n_candies))
  1. Average age of people who are going out trick or treating themsel or not = 42 years people that going out trick or treating themsel
halloween_candies %>%
  select(trick_themself, age) %>%
  filter(!is.na(trick_themself)) %>%
  group_by(trick_themself) %>%
  summarise(average_age = round(mean(age),0))
  1. Candy bar revived the most of joy, despair and meh
halloween_candies %>%
  filter(!is.na(preference_candies)) %>%
  group_by(candies_food, preference_candies) %>%
  summarise(total_votes = n()) %>%
  group_by(preference_candies) %>%
  filter(candies_food != "Any full-sized candy bar") %>%
  top_n(1)
## Selecting by total_votes
  1. People rated Starburst as despair
halloween_candies %>%
  filter(!is.na(preference_candies)) %>%
  filter(candies_food == "Starburst") %>%
  group_by(preference_candies) %>%
  summarise(total_starburst = n()) %>%
  filter(preference_candies == "DESPAIR")
  1. Most popular candy bar by this rating system for each gender in the dataset
halloween_candies %>%
  filter(!c(gender == "Not ask" | is.na(preference_candies))) %>%
  group_by(gender, candies_food) %>%
  summarise(total_prefence = sum(puntuation)) %>%
  filter(candies_food != "Any full-sized candy bar") %>%
  top_n(1)
## Selecting by total_prefence
  1. Most popular candy bar by this rating system for each year in the dataset = It is Any full-sized candy bar, in each year.
halloween_candies %>%
  filter(!is.na(preference_candies)) %>%
  group_by(year, candies_food) %>%
  summarise(total_prefence = sum(puntuation)) %>%
  filter(candies_food != "Any full-sized candy bar") %>%
  arrange(desc(total_prefence)) %>%
  top_n(1)
## Selecting by total_prefence
  1. Most popular candy bar by this rating system for each country in the dataset
halloween_candies %>%
  filter(!c(year == 2015 | is.na(preference_candies))) %>%
  group_by(country, candies_food)  %>%
  summarise(total_prefence = sum(puntuation)) %>%
  filter(candies_food != "Any full-sized candy bar") %>%
  arrange(desc(total_prefence)) %>%
  top_n(1)
## Selecting by total_prefence
